Searching for proof of love at first sight? 💞 Look no further than #Kleinfeld bride @Gabriella__George and @AnupGeorge93. 💫 It all started back in 2016, when Gabi and Anup were both asked by a mutual friend to serve on a worship team for a church conference. ⛪️ 

“Without even knowing Anup or his name, I fell in love and immediately knew he was the one,” recalls Gabi. “During the conference, we spent hours getting to know one another and laughing at each other’s jokes. 🤣 When the retreat was over, we knew we didn’t want that to be the end, but rather just the beginning.” 

Five years later, Anup proposed to Gabi in a beautiful butterfly garden along the Hudson River. It was the exact same place where he asked Gabi to be his girlfriend only shortly after their conference. 🦋 

Gabi had always envisioned herself in a chic and elegant wedding dress. “So of course, we headed to #Kleinfeld just one week after my proposal. 💍 The first dress I ever tried on turned out to be my wedding dress and exactly what I had dreamed of! 😍 

It was a gorgeous @PninaTornai dress. I customized the back of the gown to feature studded buttons all along the back and added more appliqué details. ✨I paired it a gorgeous cathedral veil and headpiece from Kleinfeld to complete the look. 👰‍♀️ It was perfection!”

This is your sign not to worry about rain on your wedding day! 🌧️"The weather changed 100 times throughout our wedding day. It went from cold and rainy, to abundant sunshine, and then back to torrential rain," recalls #Kleinfeld bride @angela_licciardello. 🌦️ "We embraced the rain under an overhang for some stunning umbrella shots and I'm so glad we did! ☂️The day was perfect and I wouldn't change a thing - including the weather!" 🥰
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Angela's advice for brides-to-be? 💡"If rain is in the forecast, ask your hair and makeup team if they’re able to stay with you until the ceremony! 💍 This gave me the confidence to run outside and not worry about the weather ruining my hair or makeup!" 💄
